  - STATE_UPDATE: {'last_reflection_result': "## Post-Mortem Analysis Summary\n\n### Build Result: FAILED (Compilation Error)\n\n**Attempt ID:** 3 | **Round ID:** 1\n\n### Solved Problems\n- None (this is the first build attempt - baseline established)\n\n### Unsolved Problems\n- **Go toolchain overlay conflict with Go 1.25.7** - The `go-118-fuzz-build` tool creates an overlay JSON that replaces `fuzz.go` in the Go standard library. However, Go 1.25.7 stores the toolchain under `GOMODCACHE` (`/root/go/pkg/mod/golang.org/toolchain@v0.0.1-go1.25.7.linux-amd64/`), and Go no longer allows overlay replacements beneath `GOMODCACHE`.\n\n### Root Cause\nThe error message is:\n```\ngo: overlay contains a replacement for /root/go/pkg/mod/golang.org/toolchain@v0.0.1-go1.25.7.linux-amd64/src/testing/fuzz.go. Files beneath GOMODCACHE (/root/go/pkg/mod) must not be replaced.\n```\n\nThis is a known incompatibility between `go-118-fuzz-build` (which uses Go's overlay feature to replace `testing/fuzz.go` for fuzzing instrumentation) and newer Go versions (1.25.7) that store the toolchain under `GOMODCACHE`. The overlay mechanism cannot replace files under `GOMODCACHE`.\n\n### Deterioration Score: **5** (Stagnant)\n- Same error as the original build log\n- First attempt, no regression or progression\n\n### Backtracking Decision: **NO ROLLBACK**\n- No complexity overload (no fixes applied yet)\n- No logical loop (first entry)\n- No strategy exhaustion (first attempt)\n- Deterioration score (5) is not > 7\n\n### Recommended Next Steps\nThe fix needs to address the Go toolchain overlay issue. Possible approaches:\n1. **Patch `go-118-fuzz-build`** to not overlay files under GOMODCACHE (modify the overlay generation logic)\n2. **Use a compatible Go version** that doesn't store the toolchain under GOMODCACHE\n3. **Set `GOTOOLCHAIN=local`** to prevent Go from downloading a newer toolchain under GOMODCACHE"}
